<para id="RM000000W8A017X" category="C" type-id="302GI" name-id="AX0YV-01" from="200601">
<dtccode>P2716</dtccode>
<dtcname>Pressure Control Solenoid "D" Electrical (Shift Solenoid Valve SLT)</dtcname>
<subpara id="RM000000W8A017X_01" type-id="60" category="03" proc-id="RM0250U___000037A00000">
<name>DESCRIPTION</name>
<content5 releasenbr="1">
<ptxt>Refer to DTC P2714 (See page <xref label="Seep01" href="RM000000W83016X_01"/>).</ptxt>
<table pgwide="1">
<tgroup cols="3">
<colspec colname="COL1" align="center" colwidth="1.42in"/>
<colspec colname="COL2" colwidth="2.83in"/>
<colspec colname="COL3" align="center" colwidth="2.83in"/>
<thead>
<row>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>DTC No.</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>DTC Detection Condition</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>Trouble Area</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</thead>
<tbody>
<row>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>P2716</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>Open or short is detected in shift solenoid valve SLT circuit for 1 second or more while driving (1-trip detection logic).</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle" align="left">
<list1 type="unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>Open or short in shift solenoid valve SLT circuit</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>Shift solenoid valve SLT</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>TCM</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</content5>
</subpara>
<subpara id="RM000000W8A017X_02" type-id="64" category="03" proc-id="RM0250U___000037B00000">
<name>MONITOR DESCRIPTION</name>
<content5 releasenbr="1">
<ptxt>When an open or short in the linear solenoid valve (SLT) circuit is detected, the TCM interprets this as a fault. The TCM will turn on the MIL and store the DTC.</ptxt>
</content5>
</subpara>
